WEBVTT

00:00.918 --> 00:02.251
<i>Previously on Royal Pains...</i>

00:02.252 --> 00:03.419
- I didn't know you were adopted.

00:03.420 --> 00:04.887
Neither did I.

00:04.888 --> 00:06.355
- You've never gotten over Christina.

00:06.356 --> 00:08.791
You set me up with her to prove
to yourself and to her...

00:08.792 --> 00:10.426
That's enough!

00:10.427 --> 00:11.928
I think we're done, Hank.

00:11.929 --> 00:13.396
I couldn't agree more.

00:13.397 --> 00:15.698
- I have to get back on the road
with the polo team.

00:15.699 --> 00:16.866
Of course.

00:16.867 --> 00:19.302
When he calls, I get butterflies
in my stomach.

00:19.303 --> 00:23.005
When he leaves the room
even for a moment, I miss him.

00:23.006 --> 00:25.808
- Divya and I have a completely
professional relationship.

00:25.809 --> 00:28.110
Do you have feelings for her?

00:28.111 --> 00:29.545
- I've been thinking about
what you said

00:29.546 --> 00:32.415
About who you wanted in your life.

00:32.415 --> 00:34.217
I think I can be that guy.

00:34.218 --> 00:36.118
- Are you looking for Paige?
- Yes, yes.

00:36.119 --> 00:38.754
- What's it regarding?
I'm her fiance.

00:38.755 --> 00:41.591
I'm... Her mother.

00:44.592 --> 00:46.592
"By moideen"

00:49.900 --> 00:52.902
I never saw my baby again.

00:52.903 --> 00:55.104
It broke my heart.

00:55.105 --> 00:58.007
- And then you saw her on the news?

00:58.008 --> 00:59.308
Yes.

00:59.309 --> 01:01.244
And the details of Paige's adoption

01:01.245 --> 01:04.247
Match when and where I gave birth.

01:04.248 --> 01:06.649
- A date and place
that were widely reported.

01:06.650 --> 01:08.918
- Evan, I understand
why you're skeptical,

01:08.919 --> 01:10.119
And I would be too.

01:10.120 --> 01:13.256
But I have hired
private investigators,

01:13.257 --> 01:17.426
Attorneys, even psychics to try
and help me find my daughter.

01:17.427 --> 01:21.764
And all they've ever
done is take my money.

01:21.765 --> 01:24.600
- So this is the part where
you say you need a loan, right?

01:24.601 --> 01:27.970
- The only reason I drove here
from New Mexico

01:27.971 --> 01:31.274
Was to see Paige and find out
if she's my daughter.

01:31.275 --> 01:34.343
I don't want anything else.

01:34.344 --> 01:38.614
But I'm impressed
with how protective you are.

01:38.615 --> 01:41.550
You must really love her.

01:41.551 --> 01:43.653
I do.

01:47.057 --> 01:50.793
- Well, I'm going to be in town
for a while.

01:50.794 --> 01:54.297
Although I may need to go back
and bid for a job.

01:54.298 --> 01:56.198
Oh, are you a contractor?

01:56.199 --> 01:58.067
- No.
I'm an artist.

01:59.503 --> 02:01.237
Hmm.

02:06.476 --> 02:09.145
- I have to say
I find exercising with you

02:09.145 --> 02:10.880
Very rewarding.

02:10.881 --> 02:14.684
- And I have always wanted
a workout partner.

02:16.153 --> 02:18.854
But I'm enjoying this too.

02:18.855 --> 02:20.890
Coffee, view, small talk.

02:20.891 --> 02:23.025
- I'm actually known
for my small talk.

02:23.026 --> 02:24.860
- Great.
Because I have tons

02:24.861 --> 02:26.495
Of unimportant things left to say,

02:26.496 --> 02:28.864
And I don't have to be
at my office until noon.

02:28.865 --> 02:31.567
- Ooh.
I have a staff meeting at 10:30.

02:31.568 --> 02:37.406
But I am letting Evan know
that I won't be there.

02:37.407 --> 02:38.808
Sorry, ev.

02:38.809 --> 02:41.310
Sorry, ev.

02:41.311 --> 02:45.047
You know, they say a sign of
a really healthy couple

02:45.048 --> 02:48.484
Is when you can just
sit together and say nothing.

02:48.485 --> 02:51.253
- That could also be the sign of
a really unhealthy couple.

02:51.254 --> 02:54.590
But I like your take on it.

02:58.895 --> 03:00.396
Is that what's happening right now?

03:00.397 --> 03:01.564
'Cause I just... why... we...

03:01.565 --> 03:02.598
Because that's why we're healthy.

03:02.599 --> 03:04.233
Harper?

03:04.234 --> 03:06.001
How is my favorite doctor
in the hamptons?

03:06.002 --> 03:07.803
If I see her, I'll ask.

03:07.804 --> 03:09.905
Smart, hot, and funny.

03:09.906 --> 03:11.440
God, life is unfair.

03:11.441 --> 03:12.908
Talia clarke.
So pleased to meet you.

03:12.909 --> 03:15.544
- Hank Lawson.
Pleased to meet you, too.

03:15.545 --> 03:17.213
Talia's a pharmaceutical rep.

03:17.214 --> 03:18.781
- Still pleased?
Don't answer that.

03:18.782 --> 03:20.349
Just so you know,

03:20.350 --> 03:23.285
I'm not your average rep
or your below average rep.

03:23.286 --> 03:25.554
I do my research,
I believe in my products,

03:25.555 --> 03:28.758
And I know Hankmed and I
would work beautifully together.

03:28.759 --> 03:30.025
You know I'm a doctor?

03:30.026 --> 03:31.961
- Told you.
I do my research.

03:31.962 --> 03:34.363
So how would you like to be

03:34.364 --> 03:36.365
My new favorite doctor
in the hamptons?

03:36.366 --> 03:38.234
- Just like that,
I've been dethroned.

03:38.235 --> 03:39.802
I've got a new drug.

03:39.803 --> 03:42.304
Just came on the market,
and it's a game changer.

03:42.305 --> 03:44.373
It's perfect for you.
- It is?

03:44.374 --> 03:45.741
- Your clients jet
all around the world,

03:45.742 --> 03:47.877
And what do the jet set need?
- Jets?

03:47.878 --> 03:49.779
Funny.

03:49.780 --> 03:51.580
But not as funny as you, dear.

03:51.581 --> 03:53.949
- Just give him time.
He grows on you.

03:53.950 --> 03:56.318
They need their sleep.

03:56.319 --> 03:58.721
My drug's called lullabrex
and it's a sleep aid,

03:58.722 --> 04:00.189
But this one has fewer side effects

04:00.190 --> 04:01.857
Than everything else out there.

04:01.858 --> 04:03.259
- You know who you should talk to...

04:03.260 --> 04:04.727
- Evan r. Lawson,
the cfo of Hankmed.

04:04.728 --> 04:05.961
Are you kidding me?

04:05.962 --> 04:07.830
That man should get a second job
as a brick wall.

04:07.831 --> 04:09.932
- Yeah.
Hankmed has a no-see policy

04:09.933 --> 04:11.634
With pharmaceutical reps, no offense.

04:11.635 --> 04:12.968
No, none taken.

04:12.969 --> 04:14.837
The only people dodged
more often than pharma reps

04:14.838 --> 04:16.439
Are process servers.

04:16.440 --> 04:20.676
Hank, I do what I do for the
same reason you do what you do...

04:20.677 --> 04:23.212
Because I love helping people.

04:24.748 --> 04:28.451
- Can you be at my office
at 10:30?

04:28.452 --> 04:31.020
- I promise, it will not be
a waste of your time.

04:31.021 --> 04:32.321
You are right about that.

04:32.322 --> 04:33.522
- Excellent.
See you then.

04:33.523 --> 04:35.124
- Mm-hmm.
- Bye, harp.

04:35.125 --> 04:36.525
Bye, talia.

04:38.295 --> 04:40.429
- I grow on you?
- Mmm.

